  <middle>
    <section anchor="intro" numbered="true" removeInRFC="false" toc="include" pn="section-1">
      <name slugifiedName="name-introduction">Introduction</name>
      <t indent="0" pn="section-1-1">In version 3 of the RFC Editor Model defined by <xref target="RFC9280" format="default" sectionFormat="of" derivedContent="RFC9280"/>,
the RFC Series is governed by its own mechanisms. This requires
a modification to the Internet Architecture Board Charter <xref target="RFC2850" format="default" sectionFormat="of" derivedContent="RFC2850"/>.</t>
      <t indent="0" pn="section-1-2">Also, RFC 2850 states that the RFC Editor appoints a liaison member
to the IAB. This is no longer necessary.</t>
    </section>
    <section anchor="changed-text" numbered="true" removeInRFC="false" toc="include" pn="section-2">
      <name slugifiedName="name-changed-text">Changed Text</name>
      <t indent="0" pn="section-2-1">In Section <xref target="RFC2850" sectionFormat="bare" section="1.2" format="default" derivedLink="https://rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc2850#section-1.2" derivedContent="RFC2850">"Ex-Officio and Liaison members"</xref> of <xref target="RFC2850" format="default" sectionFormat="of" derivedContent="RFC2850"/>,
the phrase "the RFC Editor," is deleted.</t>
      <t indent="0" pn="section-2-2">In Section <xref target="RFC2850" sectionFormat="bare" section="2" format="default" derivedLink="https://rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc2850#section-2" derivedContent="RFC2850">"The Role of the IAB"</xref> of <xref target="RFC2850" format="default" sectionFormat="of" derivedContent="RFC2850"/>, under the heading 
"(d) RFC Series and IANA", the following sentence:</t>
      <blockquote pn="section-2-3">
        <t indent="0" pn="section-2-3.1">The IAB must approve the appointment of an organization to
  act as RFC Editor and the general policy followed by the RFC Editor.</t>
      </blockquote>
      <t indent="0" pn="section-2-4">is replaced by:</t>
      <blockquote pn="section-2-5">
        <t indent="0" pn="section-2-5.1">The RFC Editor function is defined under the authority of the
  IAB by <xref target="RFC9280" format="default" sectionFormat="of" derivedContent="RFC9280"/>.</t>
      </blockquote>
    </section>
    <section anchor="approval" numbered="true" removeInRFC="false" toc="include" pn="section-3">
